  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A chi-square goodness-of-fit test where all assumptions were met yielded the test statistic <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"chi square equals 12.4\"><math alttext=\"chi square equals 12.4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>χ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>12.4</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Henry claims the corresponding <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p\"><math alttext=\"p\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>–value of 0.03 means that the probability of observing a test statistic of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"chi square equals 12.4\"><math alttext=\"chi square equals 12.4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>χ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>12.4</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is 0.03, assuming the null hypothesis is true. Which of the following is a valid criticism of this interpretation of the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p\"><math alttext=\"p\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>–value?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The null hypothesis can never be assumed to be true.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The null hypothesis is not stated.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"p\"><math alttext=\"p\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>–value is not the probability of observing 12.4 exactly.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The significance level is not stated.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The degrees of freedom are not stated.</p>",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
